Package sammish93.tbage.models

Class Ally

java.lang.Object
sammish93.tbage.models.NonPlayableCharacter
sammish93.tbage.models.Ally
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable
public class Ally extends NonPlayableCharacter
A class to be used in a NonCombatEncounter. An ally can be interacted with, and also traded with to supply the player with items.

    • onInteraction

      public void onInteraction(GameEngine gameEngine) throws InterruptedException
      A method to control the behaviour of an Ally when interacted with. If an onInteractionBehaviour exists then this is executed, and then a trade is started.
      Parameters:
      gameEngine - The current instance of the GameEngine is required so that dependencies such as the current encounter and player can be referenced.
      Throws:
      InterruptedException

    • isInteractionIsUseable

      public boolean isInteractionIsUseable()
      Returns:
      Returns true in the event that there is an on-use behavior set that can execute when the onUse() method is called.

    • setOnInteractionBehaviour

      public void setOnInteractionBehaviour(Useable onInteractionBehaviour)
      Parameters:
      onInteractionBehaviour - Intended to use a lambda to allow developers to create custom behaviours when a specific ally is interacted with. Example of a lambda created using the generic Useable interface: Useable onUse= (gameEngine) -> { gameEngine.printMessage("You look tired. Let me enhance your weapon.."); var player = gameEngine.getPlayer(); player.setMaxDamage((int)player.getMaxDamage() + 2); player.setMinDamage((int)player.getMinDamage() + 3); gameEngine.printMessage("Your weapon glows. You can now deal between " + (int)player.getMinDamage() + " and " + (int)player.getMaxDamage() + " damage per swing."); };
